From: Kamil Lulko <limakzagan@gmail.com>
Subject: win32u: allow top-level WS_CHILD editor to take focus + become active

VST plugin editors are WS_CHILD windows parented to the desktop (vst_host
effEditOpen passes GetDesktopWindow()). Upstream NtUserSetActiveWindow +
NtUserSetFocus refuse ALL WS_CHILD, so a desktop-parented editor never becomes
active/focused, foreground stays NULL, INPUT_KEYBOARD is dropped and typed
chars are lost (X50II activation form). Allow it when the parent is the
desktop; a real child (parent is another window) is still refused. The
cross-thread NtUserSetFocus input-attach (old patch 015) now lives in patch
0017, so this patch carries ONLY the two WS_CHILD gating relaxations.

diff --git a/dlls/win32u/input.c b/dlls/win32u/input.c
index c328a37d395..5ffcb370d69 100644
--- a/dlls/win32u/input.c
+++ b/dlls/win32u/input.c
@@ -2124,7 +2124,17 @@ HWND WINAPI NtUserSetActiveWindow( HWND hwnd )
 
         style = get_window_long( hwnd, GWL_STYLE );
         if ((style & (WS_POPUP|WS_CHILD)) == WS_CHILD)
-            return get_active_window();  /* Windows doesn't seem to return an error here */
+        {
+            /* vstpoc patch 0037 (mirror of 013): allow a TOP-LEVEL WS_CHILD
+             * window (VST plugin editor with the desktop as parent) to become
+             * the active window. Upstream returns early for ALL WS_CHILD, so a
+             * desktop-parented editor never becomes active → wine's foreground
+             * stays NULL → INPUT_KEYBOARD is dropped and typed characters are
+             * lost. A real child (parent is another window) is still refused. */
+            HWND parent = NtUserGetAncestor( hwnd, GA_PARENT );
+            if (parent && parent != get_desktop_window())
+                return get_active_window();  /* Windows doesn't seem to return an error here */
+        }
     }
 
     if (!set_active_window( hwnd, &prev, FALSE, TRUE, 0 )) return 0;
@@ -2178,7 +2188,13 @@ HWND WINAPI NtUserSetFocus( HWND hwnd )
             parent = NtUserGetAncestor( hwndTop, GA_PARENT );
             if (!parent || parent == get_desktop_window())
             {
-                if ((style & (WS_POPUP|WS_CHILD)) == WS_CHILD) return 0;
+                /* vstpoc patch 0037 (013-focus-ws-child-top-level): upstream
+                 * returns 0 here, refusing to focus a top-level WS_CHILD window
+                 * whose parent is the desktop. VST plugin editors hit this
+                 * (vst_host effEditOpen with GetDesktopWindow() as parent → the
+                 * plugin makes its editor WS_CHILD). The plugin's SetFocus /
+                 * grabKeyboardFocus gets 0 back and never commits internal focus
+                 * → typed WM_CHAR is dropped. Allow it: fall through to break. */
                 break;
             }
             if (parent == get_hwnd_message_parent()) return 0;
